===Etymology===
Named in honor of its discoverer [[w:Theodor Escherich|Theodor Escherich]], a German pediatrician and bacteriologist.

===Proper noun===
'''Escherichia'''

#{{cattag|Cell biology}}: A genus of [[gram-negative]], non-spore forming, [[facultatively]] [[anaerobic]], [[rod]]-shaped [[bacteria]] from the family [[Enterobacteriaceae]]. They are inhabitants of the [[gastrointestinal]] tracts of warm-blooded [[animal]]s and provide [[vitamin K]] for their [[host]].

